BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bRs8lQOZxnfZEFHu6pc4a
SUMMARY:Silent Reading Night
DTSTAMP:20260413T004614Z
DTSTART:20260416T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Silent Reading Night – April Edition \\nDate: Thursday\\\, Apri
	l 16th \\nTime: 6:00 PM – 9:00 PM \\nTheme: Poetic Words \\nWe wanted to c
	elebrate National Poetry Month with a poetry themed silent reading night! 
	Open Books: A Poem Emporium will be tabling for this event. \\nEvent Activ
	ities: \\n\\nFirst 8 folks to check in (and RSVPED prior on our website) g
	et a Hugo House tote bag!\\n\\nTake-Home Poetry Books \\nA free book of po
	ems will be given to each attendee at the door to celebrate National Poetr
	y Month! Leave Hugo House with a brand new poetry book. \\nCollaborative P
	oem Board \\n\\nEveryone adds or rearranges one word or line at a time thr
	oughout the event on our growing magnetic poem board that will be in front
	 of the stage. Remember\\\, no rearranging allowed!\\nThe poem slowly evol
	ves as people pass by.\\n\\n﻿Pick-a-Poem Table \\nPrinted poems will be la
	id out on a table (different styles\\\, lengths\\\, and moods). People cho
	ose one that speaks to them as they arrive. \\nAnnotation Supplies will be
	 provided such as pencils\\\, highlighters\\\, and sticky tabs so you can 
	interact with poems privately. \\n \\nEvent Itinerary \\n6:00 PM – Mix & M
	ingle \\n\\nGrab a cup of tea and settle in.\\nMeet fellow readers and sha
	re what book you’re currently enjoying.\\nBYOM – Bring Your Own Mug! Hot w
	ater will be available.\\n\\n6:30 PM – Silent Reading Begins \\n\\nSettle 
	into your cozy reading spot and dive into your book.\\nEnjoy the quiet atm
	osphere of reading in community.\\n\\n7:30 PM – Reading Break \\n\\nChat w
	ith your neighbor! Ask them what they are reading.\\nGrab a snack or drink
	 at the bar\\nCheck out Open Books: A Poem Emporium's book table\\n\\n7:40
	 PM – Break Ends \\n\\nHead back to the Lapis Theater and do more reading.
	\\n\\n8:30 PM – Social Time & Book Chats \\n\\nShare thoughts on your read
	s\\\, favorite passages\\\, or just connect with fellow book lovers.\\n\\n
	9:00 PM – Event Concludes \\n \\nThis is our monthly Silent Reading Night\
	\\, each month we will have a new theme to inspire your reading. Rediscove
	r the joy of reading in good company at the Hugo House. \\nWe can’t wait t
	o read with you! \\nFree admission to this event is made possible with sup
	port from 4Culture.\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-16/\n\nFrom Hu
	go House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-16/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
